                        {"variable": "wq₀", "time": 0.0, "expected": 3.895268735595633e-05}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "unstable_conditions",
                    "description": "Reproduces the upstream `SurfaceFlux unstable conditions` and `SurfaceFlux unstable stability function numerical Eq. 2.9-2.10` tests (test/holtslag_boville_1993_test.jl:182-215, 1021-1055). Cool air over a warmer surface (θᵥ₁ = 300 K < θᵥ₀ = 305 K) gives a negative surface bulk Richardson number Ri₀ < 0. The unstable-branch Louis et al. (1982) stability functions exceed 1 (enhanced mixing) and, because the heat numerator coefficient (15) is larger than the momentum one (10), fₕ > fₘ. The surface heat flux wθ₀ > 0 (upward, off the warm surface). Pins all 11 variables.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {"θᵥ₀": 305.0, "θᵥ₁": 300.0, "θ₀": 305.0, "θ₁": 300.0, "u₁": 5.0, "v₁": 0.0, "z₁": 10.0, "z₀ₘ": 0.1},
