                        {"variable": "wq₀", "time": 0.0, "expected": 8.888283688711665e-05}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "richardson_number",
                    "description": "Reproduces the upstream `SurfaceFlux Ri₀ numerical verification Eq. 2.8` test (test/holtslag_boville_1993_test.jl:244-270). A distinct configuration (u₁ = 3, v₁ = 4 m/s so V₁ = sqrt(26); z₁ = 20 m, z₀ₘ = 0.01 m; θᵥ₁ = 300 K > θᵥ₀ = 295 K, stable) verifies the surface bulk Richardson number Ri₀ = g·z₁·(θᵥ₁−θᵥ₀)/(θ₁·V₁²) = 9.81·20·5/(300·26) = 0.12576…. Pins all 11 variables.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {"θᵥ₀": 295.0, "θᵥ₁": 300.0, "θ₀": 295.0, "θ₁": 300.0, "u₁": 3.0, "v₁": 4.0, "z₁": 20.0, "z₀ₘ": 0.01},
